   "source": [
    "# Q-ball Profiles and 2D Ansatz Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook reconstructs the one-dimensional Q-ball and Q-cloud solutions for the logarithmic potential used in the reference study. We closely follow the pedagogical “step-by-step” section from the original exploratory notebook, providing accompanying explanations and physics context in each cell. The workflow is:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Specify model parameters and visualise the potential.\n",
    "2. Solve for the metastable Q-ball profile and compute its charge and energy.\n",
    "3. Determine the matching Q-cloud profile with the same charge.\n",
    "4. Extract the unstable eigenmode around the Q-cloud and inspect its structure.\n",
    "5. Assemble the two-dimensional initial ansatz for the full bounce, plotting both the complex fields and the density $\\rho(r,\\tau)=\\sqrt{\\phi\\bar\\phi}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "Throughout we rely on the modular Python code in `Q_ball_finder/`, so that every step can be reused programmatically later on.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
