    "## Model Parameters and Potential\n",
    "\n",
    "We revisit the logarithmic potential discussed in the original analysis.  Working in units with $m=v=1$, the potential is\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "V(\\rho) = -\\frac{m^2 v^2}{b} \\log\\left(e^{-b \\rho / v^2} + \\frac{e^{-b}}{1 + e^{-b}}\\right), \\qquad \\rho = |\\phi|^2.\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The shape is convenient for Q-ball solutions while retaining analytic control.  Below we instantiate the parameters and draw $V(|\\phi|)$ alongside the effective potential $\\hat V(|\\phi|) = V(|\\phi|) - \\tfrac{1}{2}\\omega^2 |\\phi|^2$ for a representative frequency.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 700x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "params = LogisticPotentialParams(m=1.0, v=1.0, b=8.0)\n",
    "omega_qball = 0.8755 * params.m  # representative metastable Q-ball frequency\n",
    "\n",
    "V_chi, dV_dchi, _ = logistic_potential_chi(params)\n",
    "\n",
    "chis = np.linspace(0.0, 3.0 * params.v, 400)\n",
    "potential = [V_chi(chi) for chi in chis]\n",
    "effective = [V_chi(chi) - 0.5 * (omega_qball ** 2) * chi * chi for chi in chis]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.plot(chis / params.v, potential, label=r\"$V(|\\phi|)$\", lw=2)\n",
    "ax.plot(chis / params.v, effective, label=rf\"$\\hat V(|\\phi|)$ with $\\omega={omega_qball/params.m:.4f}\\,m$\", lw=2)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(r\"$|\\phi|/v$\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(r\"Potential\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Logarithmic Potential and Effective Potential\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(True, ls=\"--\", alpha=0.6)\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
