    "## Building the Two-dimensional Ansatz\n",
    "\n",
    "Armed with the Q-cloud profile and its unstable mode, we assemble the Euclidean-time dependent ansatz described in Section 4 of the reference.  The amplitude parameter $A_{-}$ controls how far we displace along the negative mode.  Here we keep the default value $A_{-}=2.0$, but the code accepts arbitrary choices.\n",
    "\n",
    "We inspect both the complex fields $\\phi$ and $\\bar\\phi$ on the $(r,\\tau)$ grid and the corresponding density $\\rho(r,\\tau)=\\sqrt{\\phi\\bar\\phi}$.  These visualisations serve as diagnostics for the subsequent Newton iteration.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ansatz constructed with shape: (150, 300)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beta_ansatz = 2.0 * np.pi / unstable_mode.gamma  # natural Euclidean interval for the ansatz\n",
    "grid = build_grid(Nr=150, Ntau=300, Lr=10.0, beta=beta_ansatz)\n",
    "\n",
    "ansatz = build_negative_mode_ansatz(\n",
    "    profile=qcloud_profile,\n",
    "    mode=unstable_mode,\n",
    "    grid=grid,\n",
    "    omega_reference=omega_qball,\n",
    "    amplitude=6,\n",
    "    cosh_scale=3,\n",
    "    envelope_width=None,\n",
    "    flip_sign=True,\n",
    "    center_at_cloud=True,\n",
    "    decrease_towards_zero=False,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "phi_guess = ansatz.phi\n",
    "phibar_guess = ansatz.phibar\n",
    "val = np.real(phi_guess * phibar_guess)\n",
    "val = np.maximum(val, 0.0)\n",
    "rho_guess = np.sqrt(val)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Ansatz constructed with shape:\", phi_guess.shape)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
